BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 5502.54 of the Revised Code be 3
enacted to read as follows: 4
Sec. 5502.54. (A) "Law enforcement agency" means an 5
organization or unit made up of law enforcement officers as 6
defined in section 2901.01 of the Revised Code. 7
(B)(1) The escaped convict alert program is created to aid 8
in the identification and location of any person who was 9
convicted of or pleaded guilty to a felony offense or was 10
indicted or otherwise charged with the commission of a felony 11
offense who has escaped from a jail, workhouse, or correctional 12
institution while incarcerated for or awaiting adjudication of 13
that felony offense. For purposes of this section, a jail, 14
workhouse, or correctional institution does not include a 15
community-based correctional facility or halfway house. 16
(2) A law enforcement agency that receives a notice 17

